 Candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party during Saturdayâ€™s governorship election in Kogi State, Musa Wada, has rejected the declaration of Yahaya Bello by the Independent National Electoral Commission as winner of the exercise. Speaking with journalists on Monday shortly after the result was announced by INEC in Lokoja, the state capital, Wada said the outcome was a declaration of war against citizens of Kogi State, promising to reclaim his mandate through legal means. According to the results announced, Bello of the All Progressives Congress polled a total of 406,222 while Wada of the Peoples Democratic Party scored 189,704 votes. Candidate of the Social Democratic Party, Natasha Akpoti, finished with 9,482 votes.



